<div>
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Origins and Foundation</h2>
<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">The Ethiopian Orthodox Church traces its roots to the 4th century CE, making it one of the oldest Christian churches in the world. Christianity became the state religion of the Aksumite Kingdom under King Ezana, who was converted by St. Frumentius.</p>
<div class="flex items-center mb-4">
<i class="ri-time-line ri-2x text-primary mr-4"></i>
<span class="text-gray-600">Established: 4th Century CE</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-16">
<div class="bg-white/80 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
